Office of the Vice Provost for Undergraduate Affairs and Academic Programs


Offices and Programs


Student Success Units









            VPUAAP Student Success Units
          Heading link



 
Copy link












                            Academic Center for Excellence
                    

                Provides learning support services to enable all UIC students to accomplish their academic goals.
            












                            African American Academic Network
                    

                Promotes success and high impact engagement for students of African descent through comprehensive programming.
            












                            CHANCE Program
                    

                Assists UIC with its goal to increase recruitment, retention and graduation rates of underrepresented students.
            












                            LARES
                    

                Empowers Latinx and other students by providing support for their education and personal growth.
            












                            L@S GANAS
                    

                Academic support office for Latinx students in science, technology, engineering, and mathematics.
            












                            Native American Support Program
                    

                Provides resources for Native American and other indigenous students to enhance their individual growth.
            












                            Undergraduate Research and External Fellowships
                    

                Provides comprehensive support to students as they pursue undergraduate research experiences and competitive external fellowships, with a particular focus on fostering a culture of academic inquiry and faculty engagement.
            












